</p> <p><a href="http://www.mirror.co.uk/all-about/eddie-redmayne">Eddie Redma<span class="placeholder-loading" id="_22c1affa-db08-41b0-81f0-b627adb2e080"></span>yne</a> broke down in tears as he won the Best Actor award at this year's BAFTAs.</p> <p>The Theory of Everything actor gave a moving speech where he thanked his &quot;three families&quot;, including his own family, his professional family, and the family of Stephen Hawking.</p> <p>The 33-year-old actor was shaking as he broke down in tears and described it as the &quot;best night&quot; of his life.</p> <p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<div class="image-credit-wrapper">
<span class="image-credit">REX</span>
<img src="http://i1.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article5128962.ece/ALTERNATES/s615b/Eddie-Redmayne-Winner-of-the-Award-for-Best-Actor.jpg"
width="615"
height="923"
alt=""
title="Eddie Redmayne"/>
</div>
<figcaption>Eddie Redmayne
</figcaption>
</figure>
</p> <p>Earlier in the evening the star who starred as Professor Stephen Hawking in 'The Theory of Everything', admitted the last 12 months had been like a dream.</p> <p>Speaking ahead of the awards he said: &quot;It's been kind of mind-blowing ... [This time last year] we'd made the film, but we hadn't seen it put together.</p> <p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<div class="image-credit-wrapper">
<span class="image-credit">Getty</span>
<img src="http://i4.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article5128599.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/Presenter-David-Beckham-C-poses-with-Felicity-Jones-L-and-Eddie-Redmayne-with-the-Outstanding-British-Film-award-for.jpg"
width="615"
height="409"
alt=""
title="David Beckham with Felicity Jones and Eddie Redmayne"/>
</div>
<figcaption>David Beckham with Felicity Jones and Eddie Redmayne
</figcaption>
</figure>
</p> <p>&quot;I so cared what Stephen Hawking and [his first wife] Jane Hawking would think of the film. It's been such a dream, really.&quot;</p> <p>Eddie has been nominated for the Best Actor prize alongside Benedict Cumberbatch for The Imitation Game, Ralph Fiennes for The Grand Budapest Hotel, Jake Gyllenhaal for Nightcrawler and Michael Keaton for Birdman.</p> <p>The actor <a href="http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/eddie-redmayne-hannah-bagshawe-picture-5128786">looked loved-up with his wife Hannah Bagshawe on the red carpet.</a></p> <p>The Theory of Everything actor is known for his impeccable selection in tuxedos and tonight was no exception as he wowed in a crushed blue velvet suit.</p> <p> </p> <p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<div class="image-credit-wrapper">
<span class="image-credit">REX</span>
<img src="http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article5127753.ece/ALTERNATES/s615b/Hannah-Bagshawe-and-Eddie-Redmayne.jpg"
width="615"
height="898"
alt=""
title=""/>
</div>
</figure>
</p> <p>Hannah looked stunning in her beaded gown while Eddie beamed next to her in his sharp tuxedo.</p> <p>The lovely pair have been attending events all around the world, with Hannah most recently accompanying Eddie to the pre-BAFTA dinner where the actor wore a unique bright blue suit.</p> <p> </p> <p>
<figure class="inline-image clearfix portrait">
<div class="image-credit-wrapper">
<span class="image-credit">PA</span>
<img src="http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article5124914.ece/ALTERNATES/s615b/Eddie-Redmayne-and-Hannah-Bagshawe.jpg"
width="615"
height="924"
alt="Eddie Redmayne and Hannah Bagshawe"
class="captify"
title=""/>
</div>
</figure>
</p> <p>The Eton-educated actor was born in London, before being educated at Eton and Trinity College, Cambridge.</p> <p>He's got a Tony and an Olivier Award for his role in Red.</p> <p>Has also starred in Les Miserables and My Week With Marilyn.</p> <h3><a href="http://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/bafta-2015-live-updates-reaction-5127626">BAFTA 2015 Live: Updates and reaction from the UK's biggest night in the film calendar</a></h3> <p><em><strong>Like this? Did you know we have a dedicated TV and Film page on Facebook?</strong></em></p> <p></p> <p>
